                <note rend="inline" type="source">837.00/3423: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Guggenheim</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-01-09T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 9, 1933—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 8:09 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3. My telegram No. 1, January 5, noon. I saw the President this morning. He did
                    not attempt to disclaim Government’s responsibility for recent murders of
                    students which he characterized as a stupid mistake. He said that in future the
                    lives of prisoners would be respected. His attitude during our conversation was
                    most cordial and he reiterated his willingness to follow any suggestions that I
                    might care to make at any time. I stressed the imperative need of measures
                    designed to restore public confidence which he has repeatedly promised to take
                    but has not carried out.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Guggenheim</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
